orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

collisionQueryRange.title: Collision Query Range
collisionQueryRange.description: Defines how close a collision element must be before it is considered for steering behaviors. [Limits: > 0]

separationWeight.title: Separation Weight
separationWeight.description: How aggressive the agent manager should be at avoiding collisions with this agent. [Limit: >= 0]

stopDistance.title: Stop Distance
stopDistance.description: The distance from the path end point this agent should stop at. If 0.0 is provided the agent will reach as close as possible to the end point.

orientInertia.title: Orient Inertia
orientInertia.description: How smoothly the agent entity will rotate to orient itself.

orientAgent.title: Orient Agent
orientAgent.description: If selected the agent entity will automatically orient itself on the Y axis to look at the next point on the path.

pathfinderEntity.title: Pathfinder
pathfinderEntity.description: Drag and drop the pathfinder entity this obstacle should interact with. Updating this requires regenerating the navmesh or reloading your app

obstacleType.title: Obstacle Type
obstacleType.description: Set the type of the obstacle shape.

boxExtents.title: Box Extents
boxExtents.description: The box extents on each axis.

boxYAngle.title: Box Y Angle
boxYAngle.description: The angle of the box orientation on the Y axis.

initialState.title: Initial State
initialState.description: If the obstacle will be enabled or disabled when the navmesh is generated.

pathfinderEntity.title: Pathfinder
pathfinderEntity.description: Drag and drop the pathfinder entity this crowd should interact with. Updating this requires regenerating the navmesh or reloading your app

maxAgents.title: Max Agents
maxAgents.description: The maximum number of agents allowed on this crowd.

maxAgentRadius.title: Max Agent Radius
maxAgentRadius.description: The maximum radius an agent can have.

cellSize.title: Cell Size
cellSize.description: XZ plane cell size, used to calculate the grid size based on the bounding box of the selected scene. [Limit: >= 0]

cellHeight.title: Cell Height
cellHeight.description: Y-axis cell size, used to calculate the grid size based on the bounding box of the selected scene. [Limit: >= 0]

walkableHeight.title: Walkable Height
walkableHeight.description: Minimum floor to ceiling height that will still allow the floor area to be considered walkable. [Limit: >=0]

walkableRadius.title: Walkable Radius
walkableRadius.description: The distance to erode/shrink the walkable area of the heightfield away from obstructions. [Limit: >=0]

walkableClimb.title: Walkable Climb
walkableClimb.description: Maximum ledge height that is considered to still be traversable. [Limit: >=0]

regionMinSize.title: Region Min Size
regionMinSize.description: The minimum number of cells allowed to form isolated island areas. [Limit: >=0]

regionMergeSize.title: Region Merge Size
regionMergeSize.description: Any regions with a span count smaller than this value will, if possible, be merged with larger regions. [Limit: >=0]

edgeMaxLen.title: Edge Max Length
edgeMaxLen.description: The maximum allowed length for contour edges along the border of the mesh. [Limit: >=0]

edgeMaxError.title: Edge Max Error
edgeMaxError.description: The maximum distance a simplfied contour's border edges should deviate the original raw contour. [Limit: >=0]

vertsPerPoly.title: Max Verts Per Poly
vertsPerPoly.description: The maximum number of vertices allowed for polygons generated during the contour to polygon conversion process. [Limit: >= 3]

detailSampleDist.title: Detail Sample Dist
detailSampleDist.description: Sets the sampling distance to use when generating the detail mesh, for height detail only. [Limits: >= 0.9]

detailSampleMaxError.title: Detail Sample Max Error
detailSampleMaxError.description: The maximum distance the detail mesh surface should deviate from heightfield data, for height detail only. [Limit: >=0]

tileSize.title: Tile Size
tileSize.description: The width/height size of tile's on the xz-plane. If you plan to use obstacles the tileSize should be > 0. [Limit: >= 0]

borderSize.title: Border Size
borderSize.description: The size of the non-navigable border around the heightfield. [Limit: >= 0]

debugNavMesh.title: Debug Nav Mesh
debugNavMesh.description: If enabled the generated nav mesh will be rendered.

queryExtent.title: Query Extent
queryExtent.description: Set the Bounding box extent for doing spatial queries (getClosestPoint, getRandomPointAround etc.).

excludeTags.title: Exclude Tags
excludeTags.description: A comma separated list of entity tags to exclude from the navmesh.

onEventStart.title: On Event Start
onEventStart.description: Run the navmesh generator when this app wide event fires, if empty the navmesh will be generated on initialize.

onEventReady.title: On Event Ready
onEventReady.description: Fire a custom event when the navmesh generation finished.

distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster
